class Solution {
    public int[] sortedSquares(int[] nums) {
        int[] result = new int[nums.length];
        for(int i = 0; i<nums.length; i++){
            result[i] = (int)Math.pow(nums[i],2);
        }
        Arrays.sort(result);
        return result;
    }
}

Result:
Runtime: 2 ms, faster than 66.50% of Java online submissions for Squares of a Sorted Array.
Memory Usage: 40.6 MB, less than 90.48% of Java online submissions for Squares of a Sorted Array.
